  "severity": "important",
  "description": "A local privilege escalation bug was found in the Linux kernel’s SEV-ES MMIO emulation. Incorrect access checking in the #VC handler and instruction emulation of the SEV-ES emulation of MMIO accesses could lead to arbitrary write access to kernel memory (and thus privilege escalation). This depends on a race condition through which userspace can replace an instruction before the #VC handler reads it.",
